programme.title: Paranormal State: Suicide Possession
programme.desc: Joan and her boyfriend Tony are seeing apparitions in their New Jersey home. Both are concerned that the spirits are influencing their behavior: a non-drinker, Tony has turned to the bottle while Joan has thoughts of harming herself.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hostage to Fear
programme.desc: P.R.S. is summoned to help a family who has been haunted for years by spirits lurking in the house. Upon arrival the team finds a family that has become prisoners in their own home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Man of the House
programme.desc: PRS is called to help a grandmother and her frightened grandson when renovations on her 19th century house stir up the pipe-smoking specter of a former tenant named Alfred.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Bedroom Eyes
programme.desc: PRS travels to rural Pennsylvania to investigate a haunting that began after a new couple moved into an old family farm.?Over the next three days, hidden tragedies are uncovered and latent psychic abilities are revealed.

programme.title: Paranormal State: School House Haunting
programme.desc: PRS travels to Massachusetts to investigate an old schoolhouse where children's voices disturb a couple who've made it their home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Laws of Attraction
programme.desc: When Paula's young autistic son Michael, with limited verbal skills uttered the words "Go away scary dead boy" -- it sent a chill up her spine.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Lost Souls
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/medium Michelle Belanger investigate a Pennsylvania home; where a mother named Kathy and her son Michael have both felt the presence of a young boy and hear voices calling, "Mom?" but no one is there.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Firehouse
programme.desc: Everyone from the chief to the trainees at the Clementon Fire Department is convinced that the ghost of a former member is haunting their firehouse.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Devil in Jersey
programme.desc: PRS delves deep into the pine barrens of the Garden State to separate myth from reality about the so-called "Jersey Devil." Accompanied by a cryptozoologist the team interviews eye witnesses and experts in search of the truth.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Paranormal Intervention
programme.desc: Carol Ann stays awake every night taping the voices of the dead. PRS cuts their winter break short to help her curtail her obsession and close this doorway to the dead--for good.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Room 37
programme.desc: Darrell and Cherry, the owners of an historic Tennessee bed and breakfast built in the late 1800s, are reporting apparitions of a man and hearing whistling throughout the hotel corridors.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Glove
programme.desc: When a terrifying haunting threatens to break a Daisytown, PA couple apart, PRS is their last resort. As the investigation deepens, PRS and the family learn that it's just the tip of iceberg, turns out this haunting might be all in the family.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Name
programme.desc: Ryan Buell and company set out on one of their most dangerous cases to date - to help a single mother who is experiencing paranormal activity in a home that was once the site of brutal murder.

programme.title: Paranormal State: They Only Come Out at Night
programme.desc: Once night falls in a quaint?New England Town, a police officer's family is terrorized by demons.?PRS arrives just in time with the family ready to vacate their family home, rather than suffer the advances of these spirit creatures.
programme.sub-title: They Only Come Out at Night

programme.title: Paranormal State: Devil's Hostage
programme.desc: When a woman has long scratch marks mysteriously appear on her back, PRS is called in to see if they are truly facing the devil. But her credibility is called into question, a struggle of another kind emerges for Ryan and the rest of the team.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Cammell Laird
programme.desc: Untimely death, fear and vast emptiness await the team in Merseyside. They investigate the offices and huge construction hall of what was once the heart of the Cammell Laird shipyard.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Sutton House
programme.desc: Musician and amateur ghost hunter Lee Ryan joins Yvette as the team encounter poltergeists, fear and phantoms at Sutton House. They find a veritable treasure trove of reported paranormal activity.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tatton Park Mansion
programme.desc: The crew investigates Tatton Park Mansion. There is so much reported paranormal activity within its walls that certain phantoms must walk the grounds because there is no room for them inside.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Matlock Bath Pavilion
programme.desc: The team travels to the spa town of Matlock Bath to investigate strange phenomena in the pavilion. Once a tourist destination, it is now home to a mining museum, a night club and ghostly apparitions.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hever Castle
programme.desc: The majestic location of Hever Castle in Kent is inextricably linked to the doomed relationship between King Henry VIII and Anne Boleyn. What regal phantoms will the investigation reveal?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Rasnov Citadel Night - Part One
programme.desc: Traveling deep into the heart of Romania to the Transylvanian mountains, the team experiences its most frightening investigation yet as it uncovers skeletons and ghosts perhaps best left alone.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Rasnov Citadel Night - Part Two
programme.desc: Yvette gets the fright of her life during her second night in Rasnov Citadel. She takes the plunge and drops 210 feet to the bottom of a disused well that hides sinister evidence of an untimely death.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Kasteel Doorwerth, Arnhem, Netherlands
programme.desc: On their first investigation in the Netherlands, the team encounter spirits who were tortured or have committed suicide. Which shocked member of the team will they inhabit to express their suffering?

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song of Songs
programme.desc: A struggling pianist tries to start life again after a heart attack.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Night to Remember
programme.desc: High school seniors hope they get the dates they want for prom.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Mother and a Daughter
programme.desc: An estranged daughter is writing a vengeful expose about her mother, a much-beloved movie star.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Normal People
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark visit a halfway house for people who were confined to mental facilities but released because they were deemed no longer a danger to society.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Hero
programme.desc: A Vietnam vet is denied government assistance, despite having lost a leg and an arm.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Parents' Day
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark work as police detectives in a school. Their assignment: to investigate drug selling.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Father's Faith
programme.desc: A fisherman's livelihood is in jeopardy because of the amount of time he devotes to his comatose son.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Heavy Date
programme.desc: A young man learns that the girl he's in love with is pregnant.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Shirley Maddison
programme.desc: Shirley's lack of self confidence stems from her poor self image. She thinks she looks old. She's not the only one. A public poll guessed her age at 52. The time for serious intervention has arrived from Nicky Hambleton-Jones.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Laura Hammond
programme.desc: 34 year old Laura Hammond has a body to die for. Her stomach is flat; her slim legs go all the way up to her chin and she's got the sassy ass of a super model. According to a poll of 100 Mancunians, this young woman looks like a 48 year old!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding Her Hidden Value
programme.desc: Tracy is a real estate appraiser who can't seem to find the value in her looks. She works in a man's world where her clothes are usually more butch than beautiful. With a new job starting soon, Tracy needs to re-vamp her look fast.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Officer Hottie
programme.desc: Rosario is Mr. Mom by day and a New York City police officer by night. He spends his life outdoors which has done a number on his skin while his massive dental issues have done a number on his wallet. We're going to try to make him look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes
programme.desc: Zuri is a hard working single mother of two with no time or energy for herself. In a relationship with a man her own age who looks younger, she is embarrassed to be mistaken for his mother. The Glam Squad does their magic to roll back the years.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rockin' Mom
programme.desc: Suddenly, Eva is a new wife and mother. This change in lifestyle has found her lazy and abandoning her once trendy and hip sense of style. Experts are waiting in the wings to refresh this weary mother.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Very Tall Order
programme.desc: This part-time model traded in her big city lifestyle for a family in the suburbs. Mylene's appearance has taken a backseat to her kids and full-time job. She needs a team of experts to update her look and give her a quick shot of confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hippie To Happening
programme.desc: Albert loves traveling and trying new things, except when it comes to his appearance. Albert's bad divorce has left him feeling self-conscious about the lines on his face and his graying, thinning hair.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bernie Sharp "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 45 year old prison worker Bernie Sharp was looking 51 – or so said one hundred straight-talking strangers on a street in Manchester. One year on, we retrace the rollercoaster journey to a brand new Bernie.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Ground Down Mom
programme.desc: Dawn designs swimming pools and home-schools her daughter, but this can-do mom can't take time for herself. Cosmetic dentistry and high-tech dermatology remove the visible effects of stress, and the Glam Squad brings her inner beauty to the surface.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: One Busy Momma
programme.desc: Yesenia is a busy hard working wife, mother of twin teenagers and a toddler, who is constantly on the go and has no time for herself. It's our mission to give her the time and attention she deserves and help her feel more vibrant again.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back in the Limelight
programme.desc: As Nicole began to age, she felt she didn't look the part of a rock singer anymore and she left the stage for good, leaving behind her life's dream. The Glam Squad and our team of doctors will work hard to get Nicole back on stage again.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Gray To Glamorous
programme.desc: Recently relocated from Alaska to sunny California, drab Denise wants a new look to match her bright new future. She is determined to redesign her appearance to complement her inner artist. With some help from our team, she'll go from gray to glamorous.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: With Danny away, and Du Plessis undertaking an ignominious stretch of community service, Ed is left in charge of running the Endangered Species Project.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Ed are anxiously preparing for a review with JLW, the pharmaceutical company that fund their Endangered Species Project. They are desperate for it to go smoothly, and as a result are driving the rest of the family mad.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Following the loss of their funding, the family are in dire financial straits. Danny and Ed attempt to get an extension on their mortgage but are refused. Fiona spurs Ed on, telling him that the man she used to know would have a plan for survival.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Strange things are happening at Leopard's Den. The family awake to find frogs everywhere, seemingly having rained down overnight; the giraffe refuses to budge from the front gate and the cheetah is off its food.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New Year's Eve at Leopard's Den. Alice has returned, but the stress of combining work with caring for baby Bobby is causing tension between her and Danny. Liv is furious that Fatani hasn't told his mother about their relationship.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Scabby Monkey
programme.desc: Contending with overweight cats and their over protective owners was not what Danny Trevanion had in mind when he became a vet. So when a scruffy, barely alive African monkey arrives at his practise Danny is fascinated by the challenge.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: Danny is having second thoughts about the wisdom of uprooting his new family and ploughing all their money into a business venture that they know next to nothing about.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper team is responding to a life threatening emergency.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: The team have received a status 2 callout; Mark Lorimer was knocked out and has multiple injuries after being hit head-on by another vehicle.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The team are called to a road accident where a woman has been cut from inside of her wrecked car.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: The team is responding to a life-threatening emergency. A cyclist in his 60s, Terrence Williams, is unresponsive and critical after an accident 15 minutes flying time from Auckland, near the small settlement of Maramarua.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The team are called out to a status 2 emergency; Clark Chamberlain was abseiling when he fell from the top of a cliff to the ground. He's now in a critical condition suffering from multiple injuries.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: A monster swell has trapped two teenage girls on the rocks at Sydney's North Head. As high-tide approaches, a daring double-winch rescue is their only option – to stop the teenagers from being swept out to sea.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: The team are responding to reports of a life-or death emergency; Jim Te Whata has been pulled from the water cold, unconscious and not breathing.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggles to save two young men who are feared drowned at Hahei; a Coromandel motorcyclist is struggling with punctured lungs, and young man is trapped inside a car after a high speed accident.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: A teenage motorcyclist is fighting for his life after crashing on a remote farm near Warkworth, a man has 2nd degree burns to his face and hands from an accidental explosion, and four men are missing after two boats capsized on the Kawhia bar.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland
programme.desc: The Honda Africa Twin is back. From 1988 to 2004, it was the ultimate bike for enduro fans. The model of the modern era is hunting down the competition from BMW and KTM. We investigate the secret of its success.
programme.sub-title: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW
programme.desc: An incredible 215 hp with a total weight of only 149 kilos: the BMW HP4 RACE is a true racing bike. The model is limited and highly sought-after.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Carbon-Bikes / Ducati
programme.desc: Carbon has been used in racing for decades. But it's new that the lightweight yet very strong material is finding favour in motorbike construction. And it is this kind of lightweight construction that racing driver Julius Ilmberger specialises in.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Harley-Davidson
programme.desc: Dyna Switchback, Sportster 72 and Softail Slim were the names of the Harley newcomers on show in the showrooms. They appealed to completely different target groups, which each of the three motorbikes managed to do in its own unique way.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Honda / KTM / Suzuki
programme.desc: The 1970s are back. For years, motorbike nostalgia has been spreading all over the world. Honda once produced the first ever four-cylinder bike, the CB 750 Four. Now the Japanese are invoking their own tradition with the CB 1100 EX.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Mythos Tourist Trophy
programme.desc: The Tourist Trophy: since 1907, 150 racers have been racing across the Isle of Man at more than 300 km/h every year. This race has its own special charm.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Headlight Test / Schuberth Motorcycle Helmets / Zero SR
programme.desc: See and be seen. More than with other vehicles, this is vital with a motorbike. Lighting technology is particularly crucial to this. New technologies are gradually replacing the traditional incandescent lamps.
programme.sub-title: Headlight Test / Schuberth Motorcycle Helmets / Zero SR

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW Manufacture Berlin
programme.desc: Test report - the new KTM 125 Duke. The Night of the Jumps - a spectacle in the skies of the arena. And: 6 cylinders at BMW. The birth place of the K 1600.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Blacktrail E-Bike
programme.desc: It is the new flagship from BMW. The K 1600 GT is tested. Much more expensive than the BMW, but with no emissions: The Blacktrail by PG.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Enduro Park Hechlingen
programme.desc: 26 hectares of off-road driving fun. Courses for total beginners and real pros. The BMW Enduropark in Hechlingen.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Thunderbird
programme.desc: A matte black chopper, the purist starter bike from Harley-Davidson. The Sportster 883 Iron is put to the test. Competition for the V2: a powerful 1.6 liter parallel twin, the Triumph Thunderbird.

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW F 800 R
programme.desc: Today on motorcycles: We are testing the BMW F 800 R. A robust roadster with a lot of spirit, and even motorcycle world champions count on its agility.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Stereotypes on Two Wheels
programme.desc: It doesn't always have to be a Vespa. Three alternatives to the classic 125 scooter. City mobility in leaning angles without parking problems: with electro drive, with 500 cubic or with 3 wheels.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Speed Triple Carbon
programme.desc: Today on motorcycles: Carbon fiber on the Motorcycle - does that makes sense? We show what the formula 1-Carbon material is capable of.
